article.description: — Pano Pavlidis and Tony Felder scored 15 points apiece to help Stonehill defeat Hartford 71-44 on Sunday.
article.headline: Pavlidis scores 15 as Stonehill takes down Hartford 71-44
article.linkText: Pavlidis scores 15 as Stonehill takes down Hartford 71-44
article.story: SOUTH EASTON, Mass. -- — Pano Pavlidis and Tony Felder scored 15 points apiece to help Stonehill defeat Hartford 71-44 on Sunday. Pavlidis also had six rebounds and three blocks for the Skyhawks (2-11). Felder added four steals. Louie Semona shot 3 for 5, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. The Skyhawks snapped a 10-game slide. The Hawks were led in scoring by Joshua Petion, who finished with 11 points and six rebounds. Trayon Rumley added 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
